algorithm

1.first read the string provided,or enter the string through console.
2. find the string length.
3.Initialise
4.inside a for loop
  change the string to char using charAt(i)
then reverse the characters using reverse=reverse+charAt(i)

5.print the reversed string
6. initialise a counter to 0.
7.inside an if condition,
compare each character using boolean,check for a||e||i||o||u
8.increment the counter.
9.print the number of vowels
10.rest will be consonents,so total number of characters-count will give the number ofconsonants
11.print the number of consonants.

code:

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Source

{
int count=0;
public static void main (String[]args)
{

{
Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
string reverse=sc.nextLine();

for(int i=reverse.length()-1;i>0;i--)
{
reverse=reverse+charAt(i);
system.out.println(reverse);
}
for(i=0;i<reverse.length();i++){
char c=reverse.charAt(i);}
if(c==a||e||i||o||u)
{
count=count+1;}
System.out.println("the given string contains"+ count+"vowels"+reverse.length-count+"consonants");

}





}
}

}

